review_text:
Went here for the first time a couple weeks ago for one of the Cubs/Cardinal games. Obviously the place was packed but hey, it&#39;s a sports bar on game night..they should be packed right? Right away i noticed an attitude with our waiter. She barely came to our table, maybe once every 40 mins or so, she would only stay for seconds at a time. I was with a group of 10 people, there was no way we could all order what we wanted in a couple of seconds, but she would just walk away! Wouldn&#39;t even bother asking if anyone needed anything. She didn&#39;t get us water, or napkins, or ketchup for our fries. She had a nasty attitude the entire time, anyway we asked for the bill which she screwed up, took her 30 mins to get us the correct bill (with attitude) and then we waited, and waited, aaaaaaand waited. 45 mins later, she STILL hadn&#39;t picked up the bill. That was the last straw, I finally complained to the manager who was really nice and covered the whole thing for us. I appreciate him taking care of us like that but the service was so awful that I really don&#39;t think I&#39;d ever go back to this place. If you&#39;re a sports bar and that&#39;s how you operate on game night...maybe stop calling yourself a &#34;sports bar?&#34; 

Also side note, I ordered the &#34;boneless wings&#34; aka chicken tenders - WORST chicken tenders I&#39;ve ever had. EVER. Barely any breading, just tasted like boiled chicken with minimum sauce/seasoning. Absolutely gross..couldn&#39;t even finish them. How does a bar mess up chicken tenders? it&#39;s just breaded chicken deep fried!! 

Avoid this place, head over to Westview instead..they got their stuff together over there!

5 stars for owner/manager response to my post 7/30/15:

&#34;Our apologies up front if you ever felt like we are trying to over charge our customers.  We want to be as fair as possible with our customers.  After reading your review, we have analyzed our marinating program and we now weigh up the meat separately and then charge $2.50 flat rate if you want your meat marinated with 4 oz. of marinade.  I hope you will give us a try again as we never want our customers to think we are over-charging them.  We take our customers opinion to heart and always try our best to make things right.&#34;

They still have the best brats anywhere!

A couple of days ago, I had lunch at this Portillo store. This is my 4,983,067th stop at various Portillo&#39;s. Really! And, that was just this month...

 They are absolutely The Best. Dogs? Mmmm. Chocolate cake? Sinful! Chopped salad? Wow...  Italian beef? The best! Ribs? Wonderful, fall off the bone and tasty. Okay, I gotta balance this rave. Hamburgers? Okay.

All-in-all, &#34;Thank you Dick Portillo!&#34;

2.5 stars overall with 4 stars for service. I&#39;ve come here several times with my family who live in the area for special occasions. It has a great ambiance and I love the unique dinner experience at a dining club.  It is somewhat dimly lit but that adds to the charm. It is also nice a quiet so you can actually enjoy a conversation with the whole table. The renovations are really nice and they have preserved the history while making it a bit more modern.  We&#39;ve had really good service - whether in the bar or in the dining room.

The menu was nice, but the food was just okay with some execution issues.  To start, I had the lobster bisque.  It was pretty good but could use some herbs or something to cut the richness. My husband had the caesar salad which was beautifully plated but overdressed. The bites that weren&#39;t overdressed were very good, the ingredients were fresh and the Parmesan chip was delicious. For the main, I ordered the special steak - filet medallions cooked tableside with mushrooms, garlic and shallot with a side of mashed potatoes. It was delicious and cooked very well. I was happy with my choice. However, the problem is the rest of the table&#39;s steaks were overcooked. Everyone ordered medium rare and no one got medium rare. I tried my husband&#39;s steak which was medium well bordering on well done (his looked to be the most over). I was not surprised that it was very tough and dry.  I would have let them try to fix it but since the head of the table/member didn&#39;t, no one wanted to be &#34;that guy.&#34;

Living in Chicago, I have high expectations for a steakhouse. There are some things I can overlook because I recognize we aren&#39;t in Chicago but in the suburbs where options are more limited. However, you just can&#39;t overcook the majority of the table&#39;s steaks and get 3 stars in my book. That being said, there is potential once things get smoothed out.
